OL,3,CWhy illegal e-bikes could provide
OL,4,Cclues for police tackling organised
OL,5,Ccrime
OL,7,FITV News West Country reporter Hannah
OL,8,FNorbury went out with police as part
OL,9,Fof their crack down on e-bikes.
OL,11,FPolice officers have been patrolling
OL,12,FExeter to take illegally modified e-
OL,13,Fbikes off the streets, a crime that
OL,14,Fthey say, could be linked to organised
OL,15,Fcrime and exploitation.
OL,17,FIn the last 12 months Devon and
OL,18,FCornwall Police have seized 344
OL,19,Fillegal e-bikes and e-scooters, with
OL,20,F37% of those in Exeter.
